and they will render due honor to the remains of the Tathagata  Do not say that Ananda Do not say This mean place this uncivilized township in the midst of the jungle a mere outpost of the province
In times long past Ananda there was a king by the name of Maha Sudassana who was a universal monarch a king of righteousness a conqueror of the four quarters of the earth whose realm was established in security and who was endowed with the seven jewels
And that King Maha Sudassana Ananda had his royal residence here at Kusinara which was then called Kusavati and it extended twelve yojanas from east to west and seven from north to south
And mighty Ananda was Kusavati the capital prosperous and well populated much frequented by people and abundantly provided with food
