 Once Bhaggava I was staying among the Khulus at a place called Uttaraka a town of theirs
In the early morning l went with robe and bowl into Uttaraka for alms with Sunakkhatta as my attendant
And at that time the naked ascetic Korakkhattiya the dogman was going round on all fours sprawling on the ground and chewing and eating his food with his mouth alone
Seeing him
Sunakkhatta thought Now that is a real Arahant ascetic who goes round on all fours sprawling on the ground and chewing and eating his food with his mouth alone
 And I knowing his thought in my own mind said to him You foolish man do you claim to be a follower of the Sakyan
 Lord what do you mean by this question
